@startuml state-tui-terminal
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because a terminal-lifecycle STATE machine with signal-labelled transitions and an
'' exactly-once restore note is native to PlantUML state diagrams; colours come from the shared palette
'' (teal = active rendering, blue-violet = suspended, green = cleanly restored).
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title `vv --tui` terminal lifecycle — alt-screen setup and exactly-once restore

state "Active\n(rendering)" as Active RENDERER_TINT
state "Suspended" as Suspended APPDB_TINT
state "Restored" as Restored MARKDOWN_TINT

[*] --> Active : init!\n(alt-screen + raw + hide cursor)
Active --> Restored : q / SIGINT·TERM·HUP·QUIT / uncaught\n-> restore! + exit
Active --> Suspended : SIGTSTP\n(leave! + re-raise default)
Suspended --> Active : SIGCONT\n(enter! + repaint)
Restored --> [*]

note right of Restored
  restore! is exactly-once:
  show cursor · leave alt-screen · raw off
  (fs.writeSync; isTTY-guarded)
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Concept |
  |<#2D9574>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| active (alt-screen, raw) |
  |<#7590DB>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| suspended (SIGTSTP) |
  |<#67B11D>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;| restored (terminal handed back) |
endlegend
@enduml
